==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Shepherdia
<hw>Shep*her"di*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Shepherdias</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL. So called from John
<ets>Shepherd</ets>, an English botanist.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A genus of shrubs having silvery scurfy leaves, and belonging to
the same family as Elaeagnus; also, any plant of this genus. See
<cref>Buffalo berry</cref>, under <er>Buffalo</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

